---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LifeCard from "../components/LifeCard.astro";
import { BookOpen, Hammer, Moon, Link, ArrowUp } from "@lucide/astro";
---

<Layout>
  <header
    class="hero min-vh-100 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center text-center px-3 position-relative overflow-hidden"
  >
    <div class="hero-bg native-parallax" data-speed="0.4"></div>
    <div class="hero-arch native-parallax" data-speed="0.1"></div>
    <div
      class="container position-relative z-3 native-parallax"
      data-speed="-0.2"
    >
      <h1 class="display-1" data-reveal>Kirikla Klooster</h1>
      <h2 data-reveal>
        The only Orthodox men's monastery in Estonia
      </h2>
      <p class="lead py-3 max-w-prose mx-auto" data-reveal>
        A living place of prayer, work, and monastic community, rooted in the
        tradition of Mount Athos.
      </p>
      <div
        class="d-flex flex-column flex-sm-row justify-content-center gap-3"
        data-reveal
      >
        <a href="#donate" class="btn btn-primary px-4 py-2"
          >Support the Monastery</a
        >
        <a href="#visiting" class="btn btn-outline-light px-4 py-2"
          >Visit the Monastery</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container max-w-content py-5 my-5" id="main-content">
    <section id="intro" class="fs-5 text-center mb-5" data-reveal>
      <p>
        Kirikla Monastery was founded in <strong>2025</strong> under the guidance of Bishop Damaskinos of Haapsalu, a member of the brotherhood
        of Xenophontos Monastery on Mount Athos. The monastery is home to a small
        brotherhood of monks who have dedicated their lives to prayer and service
        to God.
      </p>
      <p>
        Visitors, pilgrims, and friends of the monastery are always welcome.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section id="history" class="py-5 my-4 text-center lh-lg">
      <h2 class="display-2 mb-4" data-reveal-halo>Our History</h2>
      <p class="text-start" data-reveal>
        For centuries, the Petseri (Pskov-Pechory) Monastery served as the
        spiritual center of Estonia's Orthodox Christians. After independence,
        the monastery remained on the Russian side of the border, and monastic
        life within the Estonian Orthodox Church came to an end.
      </p>
      <p class="text-start" data-reveal>
        In 2024, Hieromonk Damaskinos, a member of the brotherhood of
        Xenophontos Monastery on Mount Athos, was elected Bishop of Haapsalu,
        bringing with him a deep wish to establish a men's monastery and carry
        the spiritual tradition of Mount Athos to Estonia.
      </p>
      <p class="text-start" data-reveal>
        In 2026, entrepreneur Urmas Sõõrumaa's generosity gave the brotherhood a
        home: a property in Kirikla, Harju County, <strong>40</strong> kilometres from Tallinn. Until construction is complete, the brotherhood
        lives temporarily at the nearby Üiso Farm, which now houses the monastery
        chapel and living quarters.
      </p>
      <p class="text-start" data-reveal>
        In 2025, the first monk of the brotherhood, Father Paisios, was
        tonsured, ordained to the diaconate in 2026. A second brother has since
        joined as a novice.
      </p>
      <p class="text-start" data-reveal>
        <em
          >We pray that God will bless the growth of this young brotherhood and
          bring the monastery to completion.</em>
      </p>

      <div class="row g-4 mt-4 justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-6 col-md-4" data-reveal>
          <div class="stat-block">
            <span class="scramble-text display-3 text-primary" data-scramble="2025">2025</span>
            <small>Year founded</small>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-6 col-md-4" data-reveal>
          <div class="stat-block">
            <span class="scramble-text display-3 text-primary" data-scramble="40">40</span><small>km</small>
            <small>from Tallinn</small>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-6 col-md-4" data-reveal>
          <div class="stat-block">
            <span class="scramble-text display-3 text-primary" data-scramble="2">2</span>
            <small>Brothers</small>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section id="life" class="py-5 my-4 text-center" data-reveal>
      <h2 class="display-2 mb-4" data-reveal-halo>Life at the Monastery</h2>
      <p class="text-center mb-5">
        In a monastery, the day is divided into three parts: prayer, work, and
        rest.
      </p>

      <img
        src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1613906031335-d2f3fa3a4602?fm=jpg&q=10&w=1000&auto=format&fit=crop"
        alt="Cathedral interior with gilded icons"
        class="img-fluid rounded w-100 object-fit-cover mb-5 native-parallax"
        style="max-height: 400px;"
        data-speed="0.1"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
      />

      <div class="row g-4 mb-5 text-start perspective-parent">
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <LifeCard title="Prayer">
            <BookOpen slot="icon" size={20} />
            Both communal and private, practiced in one's own cell and in the earliest
            hours of morning, when night is considered the best time to seek God.
          </LifeCard>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <LifeCard title="Work">
            <Hammer slot="icon" size={20} />
            Sustains the monastery and teaches the meaning of effort, from cleaning,
            kitchen, and garden work to icon painting and construction.
          </LifeCard>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <LifeCard title="Rest">
            <Moon slot="icon" size={20} />
            Deliberately scarce. Monks rise at dawn, choosing prayer over comfort.
          </LifeCard>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="px-lg-5 text-center">
        Kirikla Monastery is coenobitic, a communal life where no one holds
        private property, and the monastery provides for all. The brotherhood is
        like a family: bound by mutual love, obedience, and a shared calling
        that traces its roots to Mount Athos.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section id="visiting" class="py-5 my-4 text-center" data-reveal>
      <h2 class="display-2" data-reveal-halo>Visiting</h2>
      <p class="max-w-prose mx-auto mb-4">
        Monasteries are places of spiritual retreat. You are welcome to come and
        see the chapel, enjoy the surroundings, or simply rest for a while. The
        monastery does not yet have regular opening hours, but we are always
        glad to welcome visitors by prior arrangement.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <section id="donate" class="bg-secondary py-5" data-reveal>
    <div class="container max-w-content py-5">
      <div class="row align-items-center g-5">
        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4" data-reveal-halo>Support the Brotherhood</h2>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Since the monks give up their possessions and dedicate their entire
            lives to serving God, donations are essential to covering the daily
            needs of the monastery. Kirikla Monastery also has major
            construction projects ahead that will require significant funds. We
            are grateful for every donation, whether large or small.
          </p>

          <div class="mb-4 p-3 gold-glass rounded">
            <h3 class="card-title h6 text-primary mb-2">
              Estonian Bank Details
            </h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled m-0 small">
              <li>
                <strong>Beneficiary:</strong> Eesti Apostlik-Õigeusu Kiriku Püha Mäe
                Isade Püha Klooster Kiriklas
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-4 p-3 gold-glass rounded">
            <h3 class="card-title h6 text-primary mb-2">
              For Donors in the United States
            </h3>
            <p class="m-0 small">
              Donate through "Friends of Lintuvuori Co." (tax-exempt in the
              USA), supporting monastic life and Athonite spirituality in
              Finland and Estonia.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="candle-game mt-4 mb-3" aria-hidden="true">
            <p class="small text-primary mb-2" id="candle-prompt">
              Drag the candle onto the stand to light it
            </p>
            <div class="candle-stage">
              <div class="cs-stand" id="cs-stand">
                <div class="cs-holder"></div>
                <div class="cs-stem"></div>
                <div class="cs-ring"></div>
                <div class="cs-base"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="cs-target" id="cs-target"></div>
              <div class="cs-candle" id="cs-candle">
                <div class="cs-flame" id="cs-flame"></div>
                <div class="cs-glow" id="cs-glow"></div>
                <div class="cs-wick"></div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p
              class="small text-primary cs-done d-none text-center"
              id="candle-lit-msg"
            >
              Your light burns for the brotherhood
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            href="/"
            id="donate-btn"
            class="btn btn-primary pulse-btn px-5 py-2 w-100 w-sm-auto"
            >Donate Now</a
          >
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1601231656153-73aa7f115365?fm=jpg&q=80&w=600&auto=format&fit=crop"
            alt="Lit candles before an icon"
            class="img-fluid rounded w-100 object-fit-cover shadow-lg native-parallax"
            style="min-height: 400px;"
            data-speed="0.1"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="bg-dark py-5 border-top border-dark-subtle">
    <div class="container max-w-content py-4">
      <div class="row g-4">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h2 class="mb-3">Kirikla Monastery</h2>
          <address class="small fst-normal opacity-75 mb-3">
            Eesti Apostlik-Õigeusu Kiriku Püha Mäe Isade Püha Klooster Kiriklas<br
            />Estonia
          </address>
          <a
            href="https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61585727948362"
            class="text-decoration-none small d-inline-flex align-items-center gap-2 text-muted"
          >
            <Link size={16} /> Follow Kirikla Monastery on Facebook
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <div id="custom-cursor" class="custom-cursor d-none d-lg-block" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <a
    href="#"
    id="back-to-top"
    class="btn btn-primary back-to-top"
    aria-label="Back to top"
  >
    <ArrowUp size={20} />
  </a>

  <script>
    import "../lib/reveal.js";
    import "../lib/parallax.js";
    import "../lib/tilt3d.js";
    import "../lib/candle.js";
    import "../lib/cursor.js";
  </script>
</Layout>
